{
  "Mean Value Theorem": "",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "",
  "For f(x) = x^3 - 3x on [0, 2], what is the average rate of change?": "",
  "[f(2)-f(0)]/(2-0) = [(8-6)-0]/2 = 2/2 = 1.": "",
  "For f(x) = sin(x) on [0, pi], what is the average rate of change?": "",
  "[f(pi)-f(0)]/(pi-0) = (0-0)/pi = 0.": "",
  "For f(x) = e^x on [0, 1], what is the average rate of change?": "",
  "[f(1)-f(0)]/(1-0) = (e - 1)/1 = e - 1 ≈ 1.718.": "",
  "What is the 'average rate of change' of a function on an interval [a, b]?": "",
  "The average rate of change is the slope of the secant line connecting (a, f(a)) and (b, f(b)): [f(b)-f(a)]/(b-a).": "",
  "What is the geometric interpretation of the Mean Value Theorem?": "",
  "Geometrically, the MVT says there is at least one point c where the tangent line has the same slope as the secant line from (a, f(a)) to (b, f(b)).": "",
  "What is the relationship between the MVT and Rolle's Theorem?": "",
  "Rolle's Theorem is the MVT applied when f(a) = f(b), which means the average rate of change is 0, so there exists c with f'(c) = 0.": "",
  "What is a 'secant line' in the context of the MVT?": "",
  "A secant line connects two points on a curve. In the MVT context, it connects (a, f(a)) and (b, f(b)), and its slope is the average rate of change.": "",
  "What is the 'hypothesis' of a theorem?": "",
  "The hypothesis (or hypotheses) of a theorem are the conditions or assumptions that must hold true for the conclusion to be guaranteed.": "",
  "An investment grows according to A(t) = 1000e^(0.05t) dollars over 10 years. A financial analyst applies the MVT on [0, 10] to find when the instantaneous growth rate equals the average growth rate. What is the approximate time?": "",
  "Average rate = [1000e^0.5 - 1000]/10 = 100(e^0.5 - 1) ≈ 64.87. A'(t) = 50e^(0.05t). Setting 50e^(0.05c) = 64.87 gives e^(0.05c) = 1.297, 0.05c = ln(1.297) ≈ 0.26, c ≈ 5.2. More precisely c = 20*ln((e^0.5-1)/0.5) but the approximate answer is near 4.84.": "",
  "A hiker's altitude on a mountain trail is modeled by h(x) = -x^2 + 6x + 2 (in hundreds of feet) for 0 <= x <= 5 miles. At what distance x does the hiker's instantaneous rate of altitude change equal the average rate of change?": "",
  "Average rate = [h(5)-h(0)]/5 = [(−25+30+2)−2]/5 = 5/5 = 1. h'(x) = −2x + 6. Setting −2c + 6 = 1 gives c = 2.5.": "",
  "A company's revenue function is R(t) = 100t - 2t^2 thousand dollars, where t is months since launch (0 <= t <= 20). An analyst applies the MVT on [0, 20] to find when the monthly revenue rate equals the average revenue rate. What month does the analyst find?": "",
  "Average rate = [R(20)-R(0)]/20 = [(2000-800)-0]/20 = 1200/20 = 60. R'(t) = 100-4t. Setting 100-4c = 60 gives c = 10.": "",
  "A water tank fills according to V(t) = t^3 - 6t^2 + 12t gallons over [0, 4] hours. Using the MVT, at what time is the instantaneous fill rate equal to the average fill rate?": "",
  "Average rate = [V(4)-V(0)]/4 = [64-96+48]/4 = 16/4 = 4. V'(t) = 3t^2-12t+12. Setting 3c^2-12c+12 = 4 gives 3c^2-12c+8 = 0, c = (12 ± sqrt(48))/6 = 2 ± 2sqrt(3)/3.": "",
  "The temperature in a greenhouse follows T(t) = 60 + 20sin(pi*t/12) degrees F over a 12-hour period [0, 12]. A botanist needs to know at what time the rate of temperature change equals the average rate. Find t.": "",
  "Average rate = [T(12)-T(0)]/12 = [60-60]/12 = 0. T'(t) = 20(pi/12)cos(pi*t/12). Setting T'(c) = 0 gives cos(pi*c/12) = 0, so pi*c/12 = pi/2, c = 6.": "",
  "A ball is thrown upward with position s(t) = -16t^2 + 64t feet. Over the interval [0, 2], at what time does the instantaneous velocity equal the average velocity?": "",
  "Average velocity = [s(2)-s(0)]/2 = [(−64+128)−0]/2 = 64/2 = 32. s'(t) = −32t+64. Setting −32c+64 = 32 gives c = 1.": "",
  "A factory's production function is P(t) = 500 + 40t - t^2 units, where t is hours into the shift (0 <= t <= 8). The manager wants to know at what hour the production rate equals the average production rate over the shift.": "",
  "Average rate = [P(8)-P(0)]/8 = [(500+320-64)-500]/8 = 256/8 = 32. P'(t) = 40-2t. Setting 40-2c = 32 gives c = 4.": "",
  "A swimmer's distance along a pool lane is s(t) = 3t^2 - 0.2t^3 meters for 0 <= t <= 10 seconds. The coach applies the MVT on [2, 8] to find when the swimmer's instantaneous speed equals the average speed. What approximate time does the coach find?": "",
  "s(8) = 192-102.4 = 89.6. s(2) = 12-1.6 = 10.4. Average rate = (89.6-10.4)/6 = 79.2/6 = 13.2. s'(t) = 6t-0.6t^2. Setting 6c-0.6c^2 = 13.2 gives 0.6c^2-6c+13.2 = 0, c^2-10c+22 = 0, c = (10±sqrt(12))/2 = 5±sqrt(3). So c ≈ 3.27 or c ≈ 6.73, both in (2,8). The approximate answer is around t = 5 (midpoint).": ""
}